sense.definition:
 (denom. of נָזִיר) 
to vow to be a Nazarite;
to dedicate one’s self to nazariteship.

sense.notes:
 B. Kam. VIII, 1 הִכָּהוּ חייב וכ' if he hit him (created a sore), he must pay for curing him. Ib. 3 המַכֶּה את וכ' if a person strikes his father &c. Snh. IX, 2 נתכוין להַכֹּותֹו וכ' if he intended to hit him on his loins. Y. Peah I, 16
a bot. (ref. to Ps. CXX, 3, sq.) כל כלי זיין מַכִּין וכ' all weapons strike in their place, but this (calumny) strikes at a distance; a. v. fr.—Part. pass. מוּכֶּה; f. מוּכָּה; 
pl. מוּכִּים, מוּכִּין; מוּכֹּות. Keth. VII, 10, a. fr. מוּכֵּה שהין afflicted with leprosy. Ib. I, 3, a. fr. מוּכַּת עץ one who lost her hymen through an accidentallesion. Par. VIII, 9; Mikv. I, 8, v. מַיִם.

sense.definition:
 (preced.) 
slaughter; slaughtering (according to the ritual, שְׁחִיטָה); 
sacrifice, feast (= h. זֶבַח).

נֵס) 
to put up a sign; to ask for a test (cmp. Is. VII, 11, sq.); 
to try, test.

